Definition: Unique lake identifier developed for LAGOS (US).
40-char GUID value that uniquely identifies the occurrence of each feature in The National Map. National Database primary key
Unique identifier. The first eight digits are the WBD_HUC8.  The next six digits are randomly assigned, sequential numbers that are unique within a HUC8.
Area of areal feature based on Albers Equal Area.
Date of last feature modification in National Hydrography Dataset.
Unique identifier assigned by GNIS.
Proper name, specific term, or expression by which a particular geographic entity is known.
Alternate (GNIS) names for the lake, separated by semi-colons.
Current name and the translated legal/statistical area description code for county.
5-digit concatenation of current state FIPS code and county FIPS code.
The latitude of the lake centroid (NAD83).
The longitude of the lake centroid (NAD83).
2-character state name abbreviation. Border lakes are assigned to a a single state.
A designator used to describe the unique name, number, or code assigned to identify the monitoring location.
The designator specified by the sampling organization for the site at which sampling or other activities are conducted.
Example: STRAWBERRY LAKE NORTHWEST BASIN, HAMBURG TOWNSHIP, SECTION 27

Definition: The source system that provided data to the Water Quality Portal (NWIS, STORET, STEWARDS, etc).
Common identifier of the NHD Waterbody feature.
Reach Code assigned to feature.
Feature area in square kilometers.
Unique lake identifier developed for LAGOS (NE).
Unique lake identifier from the original LAGOS-NE water quality source dataset. This is not standardized and each source dataset has its own system.
Lake site identifier from National Lakes Assessment 2007 survey
Lake site identifier from National Lakes Assessment 2012 survey
Count of WQP sites within the LAGOS-US lake.
Count of NHDPlusV2 polygons matching the LAGOS-US lagoslakeid.
Count of LAGOS-US polygons matching the NHDPlusV2 COMID.
Count of LAGOS-NE lagoslakeids matching the LAGOS-US lagoslakeid.
Count of LAGOS-US lagoslakeids matching the LAGOS-NE lagoslakeid.
